public class ByteArray extends PrimitiveArray implements ByteList
A dynamic array of primitive byte values. Supports the indexing operations in ByteList. Expands the size of the array if you call set(int, byte) or add(byte) and the array is not big enough.

Constructors take the same name, maximum size and estimated capacity that all PrimitiveCollections take. In addition, a ByteArray can construct from part or all of a primitive byte[].

A sub-array can be retrieved by specifying the starting index and the length with sublist(int, int). The sub-array is read only and will share data with the underlying parent array for efficiency.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
